Date: 2002-02-25

Title: A model for time-dependent cosmological constant and its consistency

with the present Friedmann universeAuthors: M. Novello, J. Barcelos-Neto, and J.M. Salim

Comments: 5 pages, Revtex 4, twocolumn (minor corrections and improved

reference list. To appear in Classical and Quantum Gravity)Journal-ref: Class.Quant.Grav. 19 (2002) 3107-3113

We use a model where the cosmological term can be related to the chiral gaugeanomaly of a possible quantum scenario of the initial evolution of theuniverse. We show that this term is compatible with the Friedmann behavior ofthe present universe.